by Aikoland » Wed Aug 11, 2021 11:58 pm

So anyways, talking about clichés, one cliché that commonly gets brought up in this thread is nations that don't really have any info about the bad/negative things about their country, which I definitely agree with is a common cliché on this site.

But one thing that usually comes with talking about this cliché is calling these nations 'Mary Sues' and I personally disagree on that front.

To me, if a nation just lacks info about its negative aspects, then it's not inherently a Mary Sue nation. The person behind the nation could just have no real interest in writing about that stuff and still manage write a compelling and interesting nation.

What I think makes a nation a Mary Sue nation is when they have no info about their negative aspects and constantly talk about how perfect and flawless that their nation is. Like they deliberately draw attention to the lack of flaws their nation has.
